 a factor of two. For a planet with a weaker atmosphere (with a surface\npressure of 97.8 hPa), the planetary magnetic field has a much stronger\ninfluence on the biological radiation dose, changing it by up to two orders of\nmagnitude.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Mar 2016 17:09:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-22"}
